National Climate Advisor Gina McCarthy recently held a virtual meeting with leaders from oil and gas companies to discuss priorities related to climate change, job creation, and clean energy. McCarthy emphasized President Biden's commitment to including all stakeholders in addressing climate change and asked participants to share their commitments and ideas for reducing emissions while supporting local economies. She highlighted Biden's plans to create union jobs, deploy emission reduction technologies, and strengthen American manufacturing. The meeting also included representatives from the Department of the Interior to discuss Biden's pause on leasing federal public lands and ongoing efforts to engage various perspectives in addressing climate change and supporting economic growth.